# Part VI: Connection to Thermal Time

## Connes-Rovelli (1994)

Time evolution in quantum gravity should emerge from the modular flow of the state:

$$\frac{ds}{dt} = \frac{2\pi k_B T}{\hbar}$$

Thermal time IS modular flow. The arrow of time IS entropy increase. Temperature IS modular periodicity.

This was a proposal for **quantum gravity**.

## What We Didn't Realize

The Hamiltonian of mean force IS restricted thermal time.

When we compute H*_A(β), we are computing the generator of modular flow on a subsystem.

When we measure "temperature-dependent energy levels," we are measuring how the modular structure looks from inside a subsystem.

**We were doing Connes-Rovelli physics in chemistry labs.**

The nanothermodynamics experiments — thermophoresis, nanoclusters, molecular machines — are **experimental tests of thermal time**.

Nobody knew because nobody connected the frameworks.

