|Anomalous heat capacity|"Surface effects dominate"|Mutual information across cut is large|
|Size-dependent phase transitions|"Finite-size corrections"|Algebraic cut changes with system size|
|Non-extensive entropy|"Boundaries matter"|Correlations across cut don't scale with volume|

## What This Means

Connes-Rovelli thermal time has been considered "untestable" because it's about Planck-scale physics.

**Wrong.**

Modular flow doesn't care about scale. It's algebraic. It works anywhere you have a state and a subalgebra.

We've been testing it at the nanoscale for twenty years.

The anomalies we catalogued are the modular structure showing through.

